response.answer_text: Billie Eilish is a PRODUCT and everything she does is the result of MARKETING. Stop being so easy to fool. Have you by any chance noticed that most pop stars nowadays are very attractive? The rock star Meatloaf is not attractive. He got to be a rock star because he had a whole album of amazingly incredible songs.  His album “Bat Out of Hell” was released in 1977 and still sells about 200,000 copies per year and has sold an estimated 43 million copies worldwide.  People like Meatloaf, who have incredible TALENT, are VERY RARE. You know what’s NOT RARE? Very attractive people who can sing okay.  Those kind of pop stars are a PRODUCT that has to be MARKETED to the public. When the record companies have a POP STAR PRODUCT to market, the most important thing is to KEEP PEOPLE TALKING about their new POP STAR PRODUCT.  You know that old guy in your neighborhood who doesn’t talk to anyone and keeps to himself? Nobody talks about him because he’s boring.  But if he came outside one day and pointed a rifle at people, and you took a video of it and posted it on youtube, he would be world famous in about 2 hours. People in Tibet would be talking about him.  This is called “creating buzz.” “Buzz Marketing” means creating online videos centered around something humorous, controversial, unusual or outrageous, that hope to cause a sensation and get people talking about it, and sharing it via social media. It’s just a big game. So that’s why all these pop stars continually do stuff that’s outrageous or weird: so that people like YOU and ME will LOOK AT IT and TALK about it. The record companies can convert BUZZ into MONEY. It’s that simple. When Justin Bieber gets arrested, it’s on purpose, it’s just buzz marketing.  Billie Eilish is an attractive young pop star product. Who is currently being marketed by experts. She wears weird stuff and does weird stuff under the guise of being “different” and “artistic”. But it’s done to create buzz.  She has big boobs. Get ready for a big shocking news flash: men find big boobs to be sexy. Billie wears big baggy clothes and says it’s all about feminism. Or something.  But she made this video wearing a tight top and writhing seductively and doing a stripper peek-a-boo.  Since feminists have stopped trying to make any logical sense at all, Billie can claim that she is doing some artistic thing with her boobs. Like that she’s “rejecting the oppressive male gaze by celebrating feminist sexuality” or some other dizzy feminist word salad. Now we have this too, another celebration of feminism that just happens to be identical with getting attention by selling sexuality.  Stop being so easy to fool. Actions speak far louder than words. Billie is doing whatever it takes to keep me and you talking about her and bickering and jabbering and masturbating. Anything to keep her in the mind of the public for another week. Certainly, she ain’t no Meatloaf. She sings whispery Auto-Tune formulaic pop songs. You think people will be buying 200,000 copies per year of her paint-by-numbers Auto-Tune album in 43 years from now? Judge for yourself:  This is a true story: I was playing a Beach Boys album and a young woman said to me, “This music is great! You can hardly hear the Autotune!” The woman just assumed that the ability to sing on-key was the result of a computer program. Think about that for a second. Are you a fan of Billie Eilish? Good for you. Listen to her every single day with my hearty blessings.  Just stop being so easy to kid. You’re not a bass in a miracle lure commercial, are you? Quit jumping at the bait so easy. Demand more quality and less buzz.  BONUS SECTION: Back in the 1980s, there was a horrible, un-funny comedy movie called “Porkies.” It was a giant commercial success because it featured a “shockingly bawdy” girl’s shower scene that featured a gym teacher pulling on a student’s penis.  When they can’t come up with actual funny jokes, they substitute crudity.  When you start hearing fart sounds in a movie, that means they couldn’t write actual jokes, and they don’t care, because the public doesn’t care. Stop being so easy to entertain and they’ll spend more on screen writing. And who knows, they might even hire some singers who don’t need Auto-Tune. Also, drink Brawndo, it has electrolytes that the body craves.   Your comments are welcome. Me no blocky you. Especially if you are an empowered feminist who celebrates her feminist triumph over the male gaze by wearing a stripper outfit to the grocery store. Like this woman. She doesn’t want any attention from men! Her outfit is about feminist feminosity and a celebration of female womanhood and empowered vaginal supreme-o-gization.

On the other hand if she was a part of the entertainment for a wedding that would be perfectly fine (and it would be more weird if she dressed up than anything else given how large a part of her image and style her clothing choices are). .. I may not enjoy her music (what little I've heard), or her voice.. but I can appreciate her going against the grain and covering up instead of using her body (and playing on sex) to sell her music. .. and the baggy and oversized jumpers does look quite comfortable (and probably expensive since she also does have her own clothing line from what I understand). And given that she’s just 18.. its not inappropriate for her age either. So overall.. depending on the setting+ its a yes.

response.answer_text: It is up to the individual who is wearing the item to define what is or is not appropriate. I think the time has past for 3rd parties unconnected in any way to determine if what someone is wearing is appropriate or not. If the individual is comfortable wearing whatever it is or what they are not wearing it has zero impact on them. Judging someone by the clothes they wear is superficial and it reflects badly on those who participate. Time to realize the clothes do not make the person. Eric

I think partly she likes wearing those things, but the fact that she feels like she needs to do it so that people don’t try to sell her body over her music says more about our society than it does about her. She still wears these things but isn’t as opposed to showing her body more. I think overall she just wants her music to represent who she is rather than her looks. Maybe it’s partly to draw attention too. Her clothes are odd, so people will pay more attention and maybe that will help her sell more records. I don’t really think there’s anything wrong with that, you can see it as an artistic choice. There’s lots of weird celebrities out there who are famous mainly because of that, but I actually really enjoy Billies music and it has nothing to do with the way she looks. At the end of the day she’s an artist. She’s not walking around naked and being indecent in public so what she wears is really her business.
